meta {
  name: 9 Auth - PKCE feature discovery
  type: http
  seq: 9
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/auth/config
}

docs {
  OAuth2 authorization-code + PKCE sign-in (the non-demo auth path). This
  endpoint is what the UI's "Sign in with OpenEMR" button reads.

  -> 200 with enabled, the public client_id, OpenEMR's authorize_url, and the
  requested scopes. Never contains a secret (the confidential client's secret
  lives server-side only and joins the code->token exchange at
  POST /auth/exchange). The browser flow itself needs a real login, so it is
  exercised from the UI rather than this collection.
}
